-- Usiminas Says Cubatao Furnace Resumes Operations After Fire
-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 2012-05-19T16:18:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-19/usiminas-says-cubatao-furnace-resumes-operations-after-fire.html
Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais
SA ,  Brazil ’s second-largest steelmaker, said a furnace at its
Cubatao plant has resumed operations after catching fire last
night, according to an e-mailed statement.  No one was injured, the Belo Horizonte, Brazil-based
company said in the statement. Usiminas is investigating what
caused the fire, and didn’t provide any further details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in Sao Paulo at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  